<html lang="en">
<head>
    {{ title_icons_meta() }}

    {{ fonts() }}

    {{ app_js_css() }}
</head>
<body>
    {{ dialog_connect(page_name=page_name) }}

    {{ tab_header(page_name=page_name) }}

	<div class="runner">
		<div>
			<div class="header">Pricing</div>
			<div>We are committed to bring private networks to everyone with competitive, pay-per-usage pricing and a significant free mode. We believe pay-per-usage is more transparent, affordable, and scalable than pay-per-user or flat-rate pricing.</div>

			<table class="pricing-table">
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Connect devices and services to your network</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><div><span class="free">Unlimited, Free</span></div></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Share your network with friends and family</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><div><span class="free">Unlimited, Free</span></div></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Connect to a provided network</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><div>$0.01/GiB of transfer up or down per month</div><div>Example data usage costs</div><div>100GiB &#8594; $1</div><div>250GiB &#8594; $2.50</div><div>1TiB &#8594; $10</div><div>2TiB &#8594; $20</div></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Provide your network</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><div>Earn 50% of net income of transfer up or down</div></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Host a network extender</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><div>Earn 25% of net income of transfer up or down for assisted traffic</div></td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			<div><br>Plans are currently purchased through the Google Play Store as a monthly subscription. Prices are converted from USD to local currencies. As we <a href="https://github.com/bringyour/product/roadmap.md">add more platforms</a> we will continue to work with the app stores to offer plans as monthly subscriptions.</div>

			<div><br><a href="participate.html">Learn about how we protect your security as a provider</a></div>
		</div>

		<div class="income">
			<div class="header">Income breakdown</div>

			<table class="pricing-table">
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Provided traffic</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><img src="res/images/provided.svg" alt="net income goes 50% to the provider"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Provided traffic with extender</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><img src="res/images/provided-extended.svg" alt="net income goes 25% to the extender"></td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td class="item"><div>Friends and family traffic with extender.</div><div>This is used when there is quota on the network and an extender is needed.</div></td>
						<td class="amount"><img src="res/images/ff-extended.svg" alt="when an extender is needed, 25% of the transfer rate is charged and given to the extender"></td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

		</div>

		<div>
			<div class="header">Payout details</div>
			<div>Payment of balances is made within 30 days of services rendered. The balance is converted to a digital asset at fair market value and sent to the wallet in the app. The current digital asset supported is XCH. Please see the <a href="">terms of service</a> for additional details.</div>
		</div>

	</div>

	{{ footer() }}

</body>
</html>
